4. Geometric and Dynamical Formulation

4.1 Interpretation Operator

For fixed $C_i, B_i$, $F_i(M) = f_i(M, C_i, B_i)$ is the interpretation operator of observer $i$.

4.2 Multi-Agent Update: The Fréchet Mean

Given $N$ observers, the collective interpretation is updated via the Fréchet mean of the perceived meanings:

Definition 4.1 (Fréchet Mean). For points $x_1, \ldots, x_N \in \mathcal{M}$, the Fréchet mean (or Karcher mean) is
\operatorname{Fr}(\{x_i\}) = \arg\min_{p \in \mathcal{M}} \frac{1}{N} \sum_{i=1}^N d_g^2(p, x_i).

On Hadamard manifolds, the Fréchet mean exists and is unique [12, 25].

Update Rule:
M^{(t+1)} = \operatorname{Fr}(\{F_i(M^{(t)})\}_{i=1}^N) = \arg\min_{p \in \mathcal{M}} \frac{1}{N} \sum_{i=1}^N d_g^2(p, F_i(M^{(t)})).

We denote this mapping by $\mathcal{F}: \mathcal{M} \to \mathcal{M}$, where $\mathcal{F}(p) = \operatorname{Fr}(\{F_i(p)\})$.

4.3 Euclidean Toy Model

If $\mathcal{M} = \mathbb{R}^d$ with Euclidean metric and $F_i(x) = A_i x + b_i$ with $\|A_i\|_{\mathrm{op}} < 1$, then
\mathcal{F}(x) = \bar{A}x + \bar{b},\quad \bar{A} = \frac{1}{N}\sum A_i,\ \bar{b} = \frac{1}{N}\sum b_i.


This affine map is a contraction since $\|\bar{A}\|_{\mathrm{op}} < 1$, and its unique fixed point is $x^* = (I-\bar{A})^{-1}\bar{b}$. This provides intuition for the general case.

