Appendix B: Proof of Theorem 8.1

We prove the local exponential stability of the coupled dynamics.

Lemma B.1 (First Variation of Distance [5, Proposition 2.2.2]). On a Hadamard manifold, for fixed $q$, the function $p \mapsto \frac12 d_g(p,q)^2$ has gradient $\nabla_p \frac12 d_g(p,q)^2 = -\exp_p^{-1}(q)$.

Proof. This follows from the fact that $\exp_p^{-1}(q)$ is the unique tangent vector at $p$ such that $\gamma(t) = \exp_p(t \exp_p^{-1}(q))$ is the geodesic from $p$ to $q$. The derivative of the squared distance along a curve yields the result. ∎

Proof of Theorem 8.1. Define $V(M,B) = \frac12 d_g(M, M^*)^2 + \frac12 \|B - B^*\|^2$. For the discrete-time meaning update, we have:
d_g(M^{(t+1)}, M^*)^2 \le (1 + \epsilon)d_g(M^{(t)}, M^*)^2 + C_\epsilon \|B^{(t)} - B^*\|^2


for some constants $\epsilon, C_\epsilon$, by the Lipschitz continuity of $\mathcal{F}$.

For the continuous-time bias update, consider $\frac{d}{dt}\|B(t) - B^*\|^2 = 2\langle B(t) - B^*, \dot{B}(t)\rangle$. Since $\dot{B} = -\alpha \nabla_B E(M,B)$,
\frac{d}{dt}\|B - B^*\|^2 = -2\alpha \langle B - B^*, \nabla_B E(M,B)\rangle.

By the strong convexity of $E$ in $B$ near $B^*$, there exists $\mu > 0$ such that
\langle B - B^*, \nabla_B E(M,B)\rangle \ge \mu \|B - B^*\|^2 - L\|M - M^*\|^2.

Combining these estimates, for sufficiently small $\alpha$ and $\epsilon$, we obtain $\dot{V} \le -cV$ for some $c > 0$ in a neighborhood of $(M^*, B^*)$. This yields exponential convergence. ∎

